06693nam a22009975i 9783110922646DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20112005gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)999355456  a97831109226467 a10.1515/97831109226462doi  a(DE-B1597)56604  a(OCoLC)840441300  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aPN212b.D96 2004 7aLIT0000002bisacsh04a808222  aHG 6502rvk0(DE-625)rvk/49226:04aThe Dynamics of Narrative Form :bStudies in Anglo-American Narratology /ced. by John Pier. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2011] 4c©2005  a1 online resource (272 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aNarratologia : Contributions to Narrative Theory ,x1612-8427 ;v400tI-IV -- tPreface -- tContents -- tOn Metanarrative: Towards a Definition, a Typology and an Outline of the Functions of Metanarrative Commentary -- t(Un-)Reliable Narration from a Pronominal Perspective -- tA Plea for a Narrator-Centered Narratology -- tFocalization between Classical and Postclassical Narratology -- tTransgeneric Narratology: Applications to Lyric Poetry -- tOntological Plotting: Narrative as a Multiplicity of Temporal Dimensions -- tOverhearing Narrative -- tGraded Expectations: On the Textual and Structural. Shaping of Readers’ Narrative Experience -- tNarrative Configurations -- tNAME INDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBy redefining established topics of narratology, research has become highly diversified. The contributions to this volume neither synthesize developments nor work from shared postulates, but represent a fresh look at ongoing issues. Some scrutinize focalisation in a linguistic framework or in a poststructuralist vein; others take on reliable and unreliable narration in a pronominal perspective or the "unaddressed" reader who upsets the tidy schemes of narrative communication. Also outlined are a possible worlds approach to narrative time, a systematic treatment of metanarrative and a transgeneric application of narratology to poetry. The sequential ordering of narratives as a way of controlling reader response is examined in one article and in another is seen to elicit intertextual configurations. Both divergent and complementary, the contributions seek to integrate into narratological categories and methods the dynamic processes of narrative itself.  aSpätestens das Aufkommen der "Postclassical Narratology" hat deutlich gemacht, dass eine Bestandsaufnahme für jene Strömungen innerhalb der Erzähltheorie erforderlich ist, die ihre gesicherten Grundlagen hinterfragen. Die im Band versammelten Beiträge spiegeln die Vielfalt der existierenden Ansätze wider. Sie wenden einige der jüngsten erkenntnistheoretischen Modelle und Methoden an, liefern Antworten auf noch offene Fragen und bieten einen Ausblick auf die zukünftigen Themen der narratologischen Forschung.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aNarration (Rhetoric)vCongresses. 4aErzählen. 4aErzähltechnik. 4aText. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDANNENBERG, HILARY P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHERMAN, Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHÜHN, PETER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLANDA, JOSÉ ÁNGEL GARCÍA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMEINDL, DIETER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNÜNNING, ANSGAR, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPIER, JOHN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPier, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRIVARA, RENÉ, ec